    "Potential Limitations of API DependencyWhile the integration with the Google Search API has shown promising results, it also introduces potential limitations related to the model's dependency on external data sources.",
    "Such dependency raises concerns regarding the model's performance stability, especially in scenarios where API access may be disrupted or where the quality of available online information is compromised.",
    "The reliance on external data sources necessitates robust fallback mechanisms to maintain the model's performance integrity in the absence of real-time data.Further research is needed to explore alternative strategies for enhancing model accuracy and reducing hallucinations that do not solely rely on external APIs.",
    "Investigating hybrid models that combine intrinsic knowledge enhancement techniques with external data access could offer a more resilient solution, ensuring consistent performance across varying operational contexts.",
    "Future Directions in LLM EnhancementThis study opens several avenues for future research, particularly in exploring innovative ways to enhance LLMs beyond accuracy improvements and hallucination reduction."
